    "updated_at": "2024-11-09T10:04:18Z",
    "body": "I'm not quite sold on the use of ordering. \r\n\r\nFirst, won't the default do the wrong thing with colocated jj repos, since it'll find the .git dir before .jj?\r\n\r\nSecond, if the cost of checking multiple repos is too high to pay, why should anyone pay it by accident? \r\n\r\nMight it be better to have only git in the default list, and force alt VCS users to update their config, rather than silently slow down their Starship experience?\r\n\r\nOr worse, won't *everyone* pay the search costs for each VCS in the list, in directories without VC, since Starship will have to check for all of them?\r\n\r\nHow bad are the search costs? Could they be parallelized?",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "pin": null,
